fields.description:
In certain situations, when Jira user is being synced from LDAP (Read-only) or if "External user management" is set to ON, upon reset password request, Jira will send a mail notification to the user with the following content:

{quote}
Password resetting is disabled for your user name.
Please ask your Jira Service Desk administrator to enable password resets.
{quote}

In this case, user would like customers to contact Jira administrator to reset the password and therefore, it would be useful if we could be able to change the text of this mail notification.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Server*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDCLOUD-8406].
  {panel}
Currently, Customer Request type field is locked in Jira and cannot be used as mandatory when moving ticket or other issue actions. 

Even when it gets unlocked within the database and when set as required, customers won't be able to create ticket, as the Customer Request type will get validated as required even before the ticket gets created.

It would be useful if we could have functionality to make Customer Request type field required out of the box (without the need to unlock field in database etc).
